==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cingulum
<hw>Cin"gu*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
girdle.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A distinct girdle or
band of color; a raised spiral line as seen on certain univalve
shells.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The clitellus of earthworms.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>The base of the crown of a tooth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cinnabar</ent>⟦br⟧
